                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12665602" author="tim_s" created="Tue, 20 Jan 2009 22:29:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This also fixes &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-889&quot; title=&quot;The current Thrift API does not allow a new scanner to be created without supplying a column list unlike the other APIs.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-889&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-889&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (you can just pass it an empty list of columns to scan all).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12666005" author="stack" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2009 23:26:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Tim.  Patch looks great.  Let me commit...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12666007" author="stack" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2009 23:52:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.  Thanks for the patch Tim.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should consider whether to add this to 0.19.1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12666142" author="tim_s" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2009 13:47:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It doesn&apos;t change the api at all, so 19.1 makes sense. As it stands it enforces utf8 content row keys, definitely a bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12666191" author="stack" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2009 16:10:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving to 0.19.1 (I&apos;ll commit it there in a while).  Tim describes it as a bug (its already marked as a Bug).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12666275" author="viper799" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2009 20:06:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tim: Can we get some updates to the demo clients also there is a function in ThriftServer mutateRows and mutateRowsTS, I assume there there to do batch updates to multi rows in one call but can not find an example on how to setup rowBatches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12666328" author="tim_s" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2009 22:40:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Billy: mutateRows and mutateRowsTs both take a list of BatchMutations.&lt;br/&gt;
The Ts version lets you provide a timestamp. We need separate functions because thrift doesn&apos;t allow method overloading.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe I&apos;ll might have a quick look at the python democlient on the weekend. Feel free to work on any of them &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
That&apos;s a separate issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12667019" author="viper799" created="Sat, 24 Jan 2009 23:42:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Question can mutateRows update more then one row or is it to update more then one column for a single row in one call?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12667026" author="tim_s" created="Sun, 25 Jan 2009 00:14:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I made another jira (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1153&quot; title=&quot;python thrift DemoClient mutationRows and scanner over all columns.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1153&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1153&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) to update the python example for that. mutateRow is for changes over multiple columns of one row. mutateRows is for changes of multiple columns over multiple rows.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12676896" author="stack" created="Thu, 26 Feb 2009 06:07:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to branch.  Thanks for the patch Tim.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
